## Step 6: Key Findings and Insights

```python
print("\n" + "="*70)
print("KEY FINDINGS AND INSIGHTS")
print("="*70)

# Finding 1: Dataset overview
print("\n1. DATASET OVERVIEW:")
print(f"   - Total samples: {len(df)}")
print(f"   - Number of features: {len(features)}")
print(f"   - Number of species: {df['species_name'].nunique()}")
print(f"   - No missing values detected")

# Finding 2: Feature correlations
print("\n2. FEATURE CORRELATIONS:")
print(f"   - Highest correlation: Petal Length & Petal Width ({correlation_matrix.loc['petal length (cm)', 'petal width (cm)']:.3f})")
print(f"   - Petal measurements show stronger correlation than sepal measurements")

# Finding 3: Species characteristics
print("\n3. SPECIES CHARACTERISTICS:")
for species in df['species_name'].unique():
    subset = df[df['species_name'] == species]
    print(f"\n   {species.upper()}:")
    print(f"   - Avg Petal Length: {subset['petal length (cm)'].mean():.2f} cm")
    print(f"   - Avg Petal Width: {subset['petal width (cm)'].mean():.2f} cm")
    print(f"   - Avg Sepal Length: {subset['sepal length (cm)'].mean():.2f} cm")
    print(f"   - Avg Sepal Width: {subset['sepal width (cm)'].mean():.2f} cm")

# Finding 4: Outliers
print("\n4. OUTLIERS DETECTED:")
for feature in features:
    Q1 = df[feature].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = df[feature].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    outliers = df[(df[feature] < Q1 - 1.5*IQR) | (df[feature] > Q3 + 1.5*IQR)]
    print(f"   - {feature}: {len(outliers)} outlier(s)")

print("\n5. CONCLUSION:")
print("   - Setosa species is clearly separable from the other two species")
print("   - Versicolor and Virginica have overlapping characteristics")
print("   - Petal measurements are more distinctive than sepal measurements")
print("   - The dataset is well-balanced with 50 samples per species")
print("="*70)
```

